# FastAPI Conventions

- All routes on `APIRouter` with explicit `prefix` and `tags`.
- Route functions MUST be `async` unless the handler is demonstrably CPU-bound and blocking.
- No business logic in route handlers — delegate to a service layer.
- `GET /healthz` and `GET /readyz` MUST always be present, unauthenticated, and return 200 when the process is alive.
- All request/response bodies MUST use Pydantic `BaseModel` with distinct `*Request` / `*Response` types.
- Wrap all external I/O calls (DB, HTTP, cache) with `span()` context manager from `l9_service.observability.tracing`.
- Use `get_logger(__name__)` from `l9_service.observability.logging` — never `print()` or bare `logging.getLogger`.
- Never import from `bootstrap.py` directly in route handlers.
